==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carcel
<hw>Car"cel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Photom.)</fld> <def>A
light standard much used in France, being the light from a Carcel lamp
of stated size and construction consuming 42 grams of colza oil per hour
with a flame 40 millimeters in height. Its illuminating power is
variously stated at from 8.9 to 9.6 British standard candles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carcelage</ent>⟦br⟧
